text.section:
A wholesale dealer who is licensed by the Administration under this subtitle:
May buy a vehicle from another dealer, at an auto auction, or from a retail seller;
May sell a vehicle to or exchange vehicles with another dealer;
Except as provided in item (4) of this subsection, may sell a vehicle or exchange vehicles at an auto auction;
May not sell a vehicle to or exchange vehicles with a retail buyer; and
May not buy, sell, or exchange new vehicles.

A wholesale dealer shall keep a record of the following:
The year, make, model, and identification number of a vehicle that is bought, sold, or exchanged;
The date that a vehicle is bought, sold, or exchanged;
The amount for which a vehicle is bought or sold;
The name, address, and license number of the other person with whom the wholesale dealer conducts a purchase, sale, or exchange;
The odometer mileage statement for a vehicle that is required under the federal Motor Vehicle Information and Cost Act; and
Each invoice, bill of sale, and other pertinent document and record in the form required by the Administration.
